-- Bharti, Reliance Communications Shares Fall in Mumbai on Spectrum Report
-- B y   P r a t i k   P a r i j a
-- 2010-12-20T04:05:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/bharti-reliance-communications-shares-fall-in-mumbai-on-spectrum-report.html
Shares of Bharti Airtel Ltd. and
Reliance Communications Ltd., two of India’s largest mobile-
phone operators, and Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Ltd. fell amid a
newspaper report that the government may ask companies to pay
for additional spectrum they received in 2001.  The Comptroller and Auditor General named nine companies
which received the spectrum beyond the upper limit, including
Bharti, Reliance Communications and Mahanagar Telephone, the
Times of India reported Dec. 18, citing people it didn’t name.  Bharti dropped as much as 2.7 percent to 335 rupees and
Reliance Communications declined as much as 2 percent to 126.3
rupees in Mumbai trading. Mahanagar Telephone shed as much as
4.3 percent to 51.1 rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pratik Parija in New Delhi at 
 pparija@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
